# Infrastructure Spec

## Scope

Multi-tenant Docker/grengo/nginx deployment, tenant isolation, env vars, and
management operations.

## Load when

Changing the root grengo CLI module, Docker Compose, nginx generation, tenant
lifecycle, env vars, uploads paths, maintenance/armed mode, or deployment docs.

## Owns

- CLI/API: root Go module (`main.go`, `router.go`, `internal/`)
- Nginx generator: `internal/app/nginx.go`
- Backend image: `backend/Dockerfile`
- Frontend nginx image variant: `frontend/nginx/default.conf`
- Shared/runtime config: root `.env`, per-tenant `backends/<tenant>/.env`

## Deployment Model

- Shared infrastructure: nginx, PostgreSQL 16, Redis 7.
- Per tenant: one backend container, one PostgreSQL database, Redis key prefix,
  upload bind mount, env file, and optional armed sentinel directory.
- Routing is host-based through generated nginx upstreams.
- The backend image serves API and static React assets.

## Grengo Contracts

Build:

```bash
go build -o grengo .
```

| Command | Contract |
| --- | --- |
| `grengo new` | Create tenant DB/env/compose/uploads |
| `grengo list` | Show tenants, ports, domains, running/enabled state |
| `grengo start|stop <name>` | Tenant container lifecycle |
| `grengo enable|disable <name>` | Toggle routing and regenerate nginx |
| `grengo build` | Build `skaia-backend` image |
| `grengo compose up` | Start infra, init DBs, start tenants, generate nginx |
| `grengo compose down` | Stop shared infra and tenants |
| `grengo nginx reload` | Regenerate nginx config and hot-reload |
| `grengo migrate <name|all> [--rebuild]` | Re-run idempotent migrations |
| `grengo export|import` | Single-tenant archive transfer |
| `grengo export-node|import-node` | Full-node transfer |

## Management API

The grengo API exposes session-scoped management routes used by the in-app admin
dashboard under backend `/api/grengo`.

| Area | Routes |
| --- | --- |
| Session | `POST /session`, `/s/{sessionId}/validate`, `DELETE /s/{sessionId}` |
| Sites | list/create/delete/start/stop/enable/disable/arm/disarm/env |
| Node | stats, storage, sysinfo, compose up/down |
| Transfer | export/import site, export/import node, job download |
| Migrations | migrate site, migrate all |

## Nginx Contracts

- Generated config says: do not edit manually; run `grengo nginx reload`.
- Unknown hosts drop with 444.
- `/ws` and `/api/ws` proxy `Upgrade`/`Connection` with long timeouts.
- `/uploads/*` is proxied with 30-day cache headers and upload body allowance.
- API/config paths use no-store cache headers.
- Security headers include frame, content-type, referrer, and permissions policy.

## Environment Contracts

Shared root env:

| Var | Contract |
| --- | --- |
| `POSTGRES_USER` | defaults to `skaia` |
| `POSTGRES_PASSWORD` | required |
| `PGPORT` | defaults to `5432` |

Per-tenant env:

| Var | Contract |
| --- | --- |
| `CLIENT_NAME`, `CLIENT_ID`, `PORT`, `DOMAINS` | tenant identity/routing |
| `DATABASE_URL`, `REDIS_URL`, `JWT_SECRET`, `ADMIN_PASSWORD` | required runtime secrets |
| `FEATURES_ENABLED` | comma-separated feature gates |
| `PAYMENT_PROVIDER`, `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` | store payment provider |
| `ENVIRONMENT` | production/development behavior |
| `DB_*`, `HTTP_*`, `WS_*` | pool/server/websocket tuning |

## Invariants

- No wildcard production CORS/domains.
- Tenant data isolation is database + Redis prefix + upload directory + env file.
- Runtime nginx config is generated, not hand-maintained.
- Armed mode blocks API traffic except explicit allowlist routes.
- Containers run as non-root app user where the image supports it.

## Verify

- `rg "nginx reload|migrate <name|all>|compose up" internal main.go router.go -n`
- `internal/app/nginx.go`
- `backend/main.go` armed middleware and `/api/grengo` mount

